goals.question: What is the trend of wheat production over the years?

goals.question: What is the average wage per year?

goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is an increase or decrease in wages over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of wheat production?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['year'], data['wages'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['wages'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.title('What is the average wage per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Average Wage'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['wheat'], data['wages'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Wages')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wheat'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wages'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['wages'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
